CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 20, 1952, pg. 13 reads: "Gets Seeing-Eye Dog - Leon Pollard, left, of 2519 Bedford Avenue, is shown taking a walk with his seeing-eye dog, "Beauty," a beautiful German Shepherd, which will be his "eyes" now. Pollard recently returned from New York, where he attended training school in order to learn how to use his "new eyes" and from where he obtained the dog.  He thanks Courier readers, neighbors and Rosey Roswell for helping make his dream come true...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Leon Pollard wearing light colored overcoat, dark trousers, and sunglasses, walking with his seeing eye dog Beauty, through public housing project, another version
